          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1583417825477-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice the<strong> shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Chop 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>red chilli </strong>into rounds, then chop the<strong> remaining chilli</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1583417831182-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1583417831182-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1583417831182-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1583417831182-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1583417831182-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> white long grain rice</strong> and 400ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>to a pot with a lid and bring to a boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for an initial 12 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1583417834086-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1583417834086-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1583417834086-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1583417834086-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1583417834086-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (enough to cover the base of the pan) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated basa </strong>and cook for 8-9 min, turning once halfway until golden, crisp and cooked through – this is your <strong>Thai-style crispy basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
